                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12623599" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Tue, 19 Aug 2008 08:18:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;add the support&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12623600" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Tue, 19 Aug 2008 08:23:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Examples:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. query by the col family :&lt;br/&gt;
  curl &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:60010/api/subscriptions/row/sishen?column=url:&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:60010/api/subscriptions/row/sishen?column=url:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  It&apos;s the same as : get &apos;subscriptions&apos;, &apos;sishen&apos;, &lt;/p&gt;
{COLUMN =&amp;gt; [&apos;url:&apos;]}
&lt;p&gt;  in hbase shell&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;2. query by the column and version: &lt;br/&gt;
  curl &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:60050/api/subscriptions/row/sishen?column=url:sishen.lifegoo.com&amp;amp;version=3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:60050/api/subscriptions/row/sishen?column=url:sishen.lifegoo.com\&amp;amp;version=3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  It&apos;s the same as : get &apos;subscriptions&apos;, &apos;sishen&apos;, &lt;/p&gt;
{COLUMN =&amp;gt; &apos;url:sishen.lifegoo.com&apos;, VERSIONS =&amp;gt; 3}
&lt;p&gt; in hbase shell&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12627276" author="stack" created="Sun, 31 Aug 2008 04:49:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 0.18 (considering lack of versions support is a bug rather than improvement).  Thanks for the patch Sishen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12635656" author="zenuch" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2008 04:50:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/Hbase/HbaseRest&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/Hbase/HbaseRest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GET /&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;table_name&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;/row/&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;row_key&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;/timestamps&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;St.Ack comment: Currently not supported in native hbase client but we should add it&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How soon to appear the given possibility?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12635662" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2008 05:22:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Zinnur:  Did you ask your question out on the list?  You&apos;re not going to make friends polluting all issues that are slightly related.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do know of anyone working to implement the above.  Do you need it?  I think the issue is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-31&quot; title=&quot;Add means of getting the timestamps for all cell versions: e.g. long [] getVersions(row, column)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-31&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-31&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  I do not think any one is working on it at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12635671" author="zenuch" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2008 06:00:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I have removed my comments in similar themes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;Do you need it?&lt;br/&gt;
Yes the given functionality is necessary for me&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(At present I write a php class realising Rest API)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;I do not think any one is working on it at the moment.&lt;br/&gt;
Functionality really necessary, it is a pity that nobody is engaged in it&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
